# Copy to .env and adjust if your docker engine isn't Docker Desktop.
#
# Docker Desktop (default):
#   leave unset or use host.docker.internal:9090
#
# Podman on Windows (WSL2 backend):
#   set this to the WSL gateway IP that the Podman machine sees:
#     podman machine ssh "ip route | awk '/default/{print \$3}'"
#   Then add :9090. Typical value: 172.x.y.1:9090
#
# Podman / Docker on Linux:
#   leave unset (host.docker.internal:host-gateway resolves to the bridge
#   gateway which routes to the host on Linux Docker; on rootless Podman
#   you may need 10.0.2.2:9090 — slirp4netns's host alias).
#
# Linux Docker daemon over a remote ephemerd:
#   <ephemerd-host-ip>:9090

# EPHEMERD_TARGET=host.docker.internal:9090
